<p class="MsoNormal">I am trying to survey the collective algorithms in Open MPI.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">I looked at the src code but could not make out the guts of the communication algorithms.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">There are some open mpi papers but not detailed, where they talk about what algorithms are using in certain collectives.<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Has anybody done this sort of work, or point me to a paper?<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>
<p class="MsoNormal">Basically, for a given collective operation, what are:<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><![if !supportLists]><span style="mso-list:Ignore">a)<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]>Communication algorithm being used for a given criteria (i.e. message size or np)<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1"><![if !supportLists]><span style="mso-list:Ignore">b)<span style="font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span><![endif]>What is theoretical algorithm cost<o:p></o:p></p>
